Joy's Noodle Shop is a fixture in Lakeview. It is a well-know and respected place for Thai and Thai-inspired dishes,  and its' status as  BYOB establishment makes it a popular place. The food is nicely done and consistent between visits. The kitchen does not play with recipes to make adjustments that alter the result. The Rama Special (a wonderful chicken dish with broccoli and a rich peanut sauce) might vary depending on the quality of the broccoli, but its constant good taste makes it a dish to recommend. LIkewise, the Panang Noodles are amazing: large, crisp noodles and chicken, with a red curry, an appealing choice for many. It's possible to substitute tofu or shrimp in this and most dishes, sometimes with a slight upcharge. One soup stands apart, the Tom Ka. This coconut-based soup includes large, delicious mushrooms, sliced onions, and chicken or tofu -- either protein is fine. The dash of paprika adds the heat and the appeal of this remarkable soup. Golden Noodles, Cashew Chicken, and other selections all have their appeal, and it's worth returning to Joy's to try a different item each time or to bring friends, so that you can share some of the flavors Joy's has to offer. Appetizers are outstanding. Start with the combination platter, which can be shared by two or three. If you are alone, that combination platter can be a meal in itself.  Service is good and quite attentive. The space is large and comfortable, without the closely-set tables often found in some parts of Lakeview and elsewhere in the north end.

Joy's is super speedy...great food, BYOB! Not the friendliest staff, but the food is good, cheap & fast!
best crab rangoons super speedy delivery awesome!! great!! never better!!

Joy's occupies that enviable position of perfect neighborhood hub.  The food is very good and there's plenty of it.  There's enough variety to satisfy all tastes.  It's a local joint, with lots of families, regulars, and neighbors in need of some comfort asian food.  You get exactly what you pay for, and the staff is friendly.  Eating at Joy's feels like eating somewhere that's always been there and always will be.
Joy's Noodles is my FAVORITE thai place in chicago. I've had a bunch of different places but this is by far the best. Try their garlic noodles fantastic! Go to joy's you won't be dissapointed.

i have had a very hit or miss experience with joy's. in general they are very fast and the food is usually delicious! however, i've had times when i've gone where the food was overly greasy and/or the servers were very rude. i like to go there, but have gone there less in the past year because of the inconsistency. i would recommend them on a good day or if you want something quick and firly good. i wouldn't risk going here with out of town guests though.

I am not too impressed with the food as described by other customers.  The price is not worth the quality of food.   Decor is good. What is nice is there is no wait.  It is also easy to find a parking.
good food at a great price.  Check it out for a good meal in lakeview.
We have celebrated so many birthdays and events here, and the staff is always amazing and courteous. The food never disappoints and it is an amazing deal for the money!
Delivery Time takes along time to deliver.
i really enjoy the food and really love it there.. good for a weeks entertainment

Typical asian restaurant here with authentic fare for everyone. The noodles are really the must try here. The servers are what you would expect from a typical asian place though so do not expect too much
this is more than your average asian food. reasonably priced and the taste is awesome.

This is one of my favorite places in town for a light and simple meal.  The food is always good and inexpensive.  And it is easy to order from home as well -- the food comes very quickly and if over $15 you can ask for tree baby egg rolls -- my favorite treat!
I always get the spinach noodles with chicken.  Delicious and incredibly FAST service.
The pad thai is amazing! byob, greeen curry is great too, definitely recommended
Great crazy spicy noodles

Best Thai food in Lakeview, hands down.  Convenient location with outdoor seating (both sidewalk and back patio)!  The food at Joy's is always fabulous--there's a large selection and portions are enough to take home for a snack later.  I don't think I've ever waited longer than 7 minutes from the time I ordered my food to the time it arrived at my table.  Joy's is my favorite take-out option in the area as well.
Great for carry out. Always has quick service when I call in. Try the chicken Pad Thai. Easily serves 2 people.
Joy's never disappoints., The food is always consistently good and the service is speedy. This is my favorite BYOB joint in Lakeview. I would highly recommend the pad prik if you like spicy food!
Joy's is a great, cheap neighborhood Thai spot. Good for a casual dinner with a group, and BYO is always a bonus. Pad Thai is obviously where it's at.

We hosted our rehearsal dinner at Joys in 2011. It was so exciting to actually work with the owners on setting up the dinner. We were in constant contact with her and even had a great meeting before the big event. We love the food. Try the Spring Rolls, they are really unique and fantastic. It's BYOB, so you can get a bottle of wine and bring it into the restaurant! If you are in the area, please visit Joy's Noodles and Rice. It's such a great place!

Great place for a hangout on a Sunday. I recommend the Coconut chicken curry! and it's BYOB and and there eggrolls are small and snacksized! also you have to go to the lunch special during the week. A+
Really like the food here. The portion sizes are so huge, you can easily split one entree with someone else! They have an inside and an outside patio when the weather is nice :)
I used to really lie this place. It has certainly  gone down hill since the god ole days!  I always feel like I am bothering the wait staff just by walking in the door?

There's nothing like cheap, reliable, tasty Thai food.  This will be the best $7.50 you've ever spent.  Favorites include pad thai, pad see eiw, satay and crab rangoon.  I'll never understand how they are able to serve it so quickly.  This place doesn't disappoint.

Unfortunately, I came away with a very poor impression of Joy's Noodles & Rice. My wife and I were walking along Broadway looking for a place to have dinner and seeing the crowd that was in Joy's, we figured that it should be pretty good.  I had the fried thick wide noodles. That was a major mistake. To be honest, I didn't quite know what I was ordering, but being a rather adventurous person food wise, willing to try something new, I figured that it couldn't be too bad. I was wrong. I got served a plate of fried dough basically, with a little bit of really thick curry and some meat. I tried a few bites, didn't like it and tried to soldier on to finish my plate, eventually giving up at the half way mark. The fried dough was dry and tasteless and the curry was overpoweringly sweet. it made for a very weird and unsavory taste in my mouth bite after bite. It was dry, thick, chewy and overly sweet. ugh. It was so bad that I decided not to box the remaining portion.  The service was good, atmosphere lovely but my dining experience was sorely let down by the quality of the food. Maybe I ordered the wrong dish, maybe other dishes might be better but it would take a lot to convince me to try it again.
The Drunken Noodles is where it is at! It is also byob, so do it! Staff is nice and attentive. Make sure you go before the dinner hour.

Over the years Joy's has taken me on a roller coaster ride. It started with amazingly flavorful food, spicy and seasoned and has ended with me wondering what happened? Over the past few times I have visited Joy's the food has seem to depreciated. Possibly it is there vendor or need to cut costs...but whatever it is, my Spicy Chili Noodles with Beef have gotten the blunt of the blow. They generally have great service and fast delivery. Dine outside in the back patio for extra privacy.
Byob Thai for the win.
Love the outdoor seating in the summer. Food is pretty good and comes out quickly. Reasonably priced. And it's BYOB. Great place to bring a bunch of beers and friends.

Joys has been a staple Lakeview Thai pick for years! I love their crab Rangoon, chicken pad Thai, masuman curry and so many other dishes. Very reasonably priced and great quality!  Don't overlook joys for lunch!
Solid Thai food!

Very fast service!! Yummy Thai iced tea.  Enjoyed the pad woo sen, perhaps a little greasy but delicious and good portion for the price.   Spring rolls where ok. I enjoyed the rolls with crab meat and shrimp more!
